Description: The flight into Egypt, at lower right a young boy rests with his feet on a dog. c.1535 Woodcut
Curator's comments: See D. Rosand and M. Muraro, 'Titian and the Venetian Woodcut', 1976-1977, n.70. This is a later edition of the print. The earlier edition carries a monogramatic device on the face of the block in the foreground.
Acquisition name: Bequeathed by: Sir Hans Sloane (traces of letters HS apparently visible in Philipe's oval blindstamp)
Previous owner: Previous owner/ex-collection: William Courten (letters apparently in his handwriting on verso bottom right)
